Version 0.7.1


Version 0.6.2 (15Mar2020)

   - Fixed package problem (simplicial.file not being included)

Version 0.6.1 (15Mar2020)

   - Added a paper for the Journal of Open Source Software for the library
   - Added various extra references to the bibliography
   - Simplified some of the operations
   - Improved copying to work with sub-classing
   - Added filtrations
   - Added generator functions for common structures, refactoring a little
     out of the SimplicialComplex class
   - Added numpy types on boundary matrices to reduce memory footprint

Version 0.5.1 (19Sep2019)

   - Refactored internally to use boundary matrices
   - Improved exception handling in a few places
   - Changed TriangularLatticeEmbedding to embed any complex as
     a lattice, relying on simplex order rather than names
   - Python 2.7 and 3.7 compatibility, with tox tests
   - Improved test coverage
   - Moved to non-versioned requirements
   - Added a tutorial to the documentation

Version 0.4.3 (24Dec2017)

   - Maintenance release to move API documentation to
     readthedocs.org

Version 0.4.2 (24Dec2017)

   - Maintenance release to fix a problem with the manifest

Version 0.4.1 (23Dec2017)

   - Added computations for boundary operators and Betti numbers
   - Added references and acknowledgements to Rob Ghrist,
     Jeremy Kun, and Herbert Edelsbrunner
   - Added embeddings
   - Added flag complex generation
   - Added Vietoris-Rips complex generation from embeddings

Version 0.3.1 (8May2017)

   - Fixed some obscure bugs
   - Added persistence to and from JSON

Version 0.2.1 (5Apr2017)

   - Added triangular lattices
   - Added drawing functions

Version 0.1.1 (8Mar2017)

   - Initial representation
   - First attempt at documentation
